  "title": "Question on the page \"hits\"",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js. I could not find what I was looking for on the page \"[hits](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/hits.html)\".\r\n\r\nI am using hit-template for results, but i am unable to apply condition. If record does not contain profile_image then my view gets disturb. How to use image thumbnail if profile_image does not exist.\r\nHits widget: \r\nsearch.addWidget(\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.hits({\r\n    container: '#hits',\r\n    templates: {\r\n      item: document.getElementById('hit-template').innerHTML,\r\n      empty: \"<div class='alert alert-info alert-margin'>We didn't find any results for the search <em>\\\"{{query}}\\\"</em></div>\"\r\n    }\r\n  })\r\n);\r\nHit Template:\r\n\r\n\t\t<a href=\"/search/{{x_id}}\">\r\n\t\t\t<img src=\"{{profile_image}}\" class=\"\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\">\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\t\t<div class=\"caption\">\r\n\t\t\t\t<p class=\"hit-name\"><strong>{{{profile_name}}}</strong></p>\r\n\t\t\t\t<p class=\"hit-name\">Age: {{{age}}} </p>\r\n\t\t\t\t<p><button class=\"btn btn-success btn-block btn-fill\">View Profile</button></p>\r\n\t\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t</a>\r\n",
